This group of borrowers consists of five members, all residents of Siem Reap Province. The group is led by Tuk M., 41, a humble villager and the mother of two children, both single and under her care. To earn a living, Tuk M. sells a variety of sweets made from soybean, pumpkin, gelatin, etc., to the people in the commune. She has another financial earner who is a porter in the local busy market and is also a taxi driver. Tuk M. is requesting a loan to mend and decorate her old house, the additiO. of which will facilitate her business operatiO.. The other four members are: 
Mrs. T., 30, a laborer seeking a loan to buy planks for her house; 
Mrs. P. 33, a laborer requesting a loan to decorate her old house;
Mrs. S., 36, a fresh water shell seller looking for a loan to buy poles for her house;
Mrs. O., 36, a room cleaner requesting a loan to renovate her house.
